title.jp: Ore wa Luffy! Kaizoku Ou ni Naru Otoko Da!

synopsis: A group of pirates lead by Alvida plunder a ship, only to find a barrel which contains a strange boy named Luffy. Luffy is on a mission to find the legendary treasure "One Piece" and he befriends the ship's cabin-boy, Coby, who actually wants to become a marine officer. Luffy defeats Alvida and the two journey on in search of crewmates.

title.jp: Daikengou Arawaru! Kaizokugari Roronoa Zoro

synopsis: Luffy and Coby arrive at Shell Island, a Marine base. They meet the bounty hunter Roronoa Zoro, held under arrest by the infamous marine, Captain Morgan, and his son Helmeppo.

title.jp: Morgan vs. Luffy! Nazo no Bishoujo wa Dare?

synopsis: Luffy convinces Zoro to join his crew, but they must first defeat Captain Morgan. After freeing the island from Morgan's oppressive rule, Coby is accepted as a marine while the other two continue on their journey.

title.jp: Luffy no Kako! Akagami no Shanks Toujou

synopsis: Out on the sea, Luffy almost loses his hat and reflects on his past, and how a pirate named Shanks influenced him. Afterwards, Luffy meets Nami, and Buggy the Clown's men.

title.jp: Kyoufu Nazo no Chikara! Kaizoku Douke Buggy-senchou!

synopsis: In order to save herself and steal a map to the Grand Line, Nami tricks Luffy into allowing her to turn him over to Buggy.

title.jp: Zettai Zetsumei! Moujuutsukai Mohji VS Luffy!

synopsis: Mohji and Richie show up for revenge after Buggy's humiliating defeat in the previous episode, and Luffy meets a small dog guarding his master's store, even though he knows that he is long dead.

title.jp: Souzetsu Kettou! Kengou Zoro vs Kyokugei no Cabaji!

synopsis: Enraged by the actions of Buggy's crew, the city's mayor rushes to fight Buggy himself, but the Straw Hat Pirates come to his rescue. Zoro fights Cabaji, despite still being wounded from his previous encounter with Buggy, while Luffy faces the clown pirate himself and Nami searches for the map to the Grand Line.

title.jp: Shousha wa Dotchi? Akuma no Mi no Nouryoku Taiketsu!

synopsis: Buggy's link to Shanks is revealed, and when he rips the straw hat Shanks gave Luffy, his rage knows no bounds. Who will win in this clash between Devil Fruit users?

title.jp: Seigi no Usotsuki? Captain Usopp

synopsis: Luffy, Zoro, and Nami arrive at an island hoping to obtain a ship and crew, but the three are quickly confronted with the blustering Captain Usopp - who has a connection to Luffy's past.

title.jp: Shijou Saikyou no Hen na Yatsu! Saiminjutsushi Jango

synopsis: Luffy follows Usopp to the mansion and encounters the brutal pirate Captain Kuro. The scoundrel plans to claim Kaya's fortune and live the stolen life of luxury.

title.jp: Inbou wo Abake! Kaizoku Shitsuji Captain Kuro

synopsis: Usopp spreads word of Kuro's evil plot and the impending pirate attack, but no one believes his warnings. The Straw Hat Pirates decide to help Usopp put a stop to the dastardly scheme.

title.jp: Gekitotsu! Kuroneko Kaizoku-dan Sakamichi no Daikoubou!

synopsis: Luffy and crew seek to best Captain Kuro, but they've prepared their defense on the wrong side of the island! All looks grim now that Usopp must face off against the Black Cat Pirates alone.

title.jp: Kyoufu no Futarigumi! Nyaban Brothers VS Zoro

synopsis: In an effort to save Usopp's village, the Straw Hat Pirates seek to block the marauders' path from the sea. With Luffy out of the battle, Zoro must face the fearsome Meowban Brothers!

title.jp: Luffy Fukkatsu! Kaya-ojousama no Kesshi no Teikou

synopsis: Nami manages to rescue Zoro's missing swords and attempts to revive Luffy. With one of the Meowban brothers down, the other rages on even more fiercely than before!

title.jp: Kuro wo Taose! Otoko Usopp Namida no Ketsui!

synopsis: Usopp's friends run away with the heiress Kaya. Jango races off after them, but not before sending Butchie into a berserk rage. As Zoro continues his battle, Luffy takes on Captain Kuro.

title.jp: Kayaw wo Mamore! Usopp Kaizoku-dan dai Katsuyaku!

synopsis: Luffy battles with Kuro on the beach, while the Veggies (with Kaya in tow) flee Jango the Hypnotist.

title.jp: Ikari Bakuhatsu! Kuro vs Luffy Ketchaku no Yukue!

synopsis: Kaya rewards the Straw Hat Pirates' efforts to save her with a ship to call their own - the Going Merry!

title.jp: Anta ga Chinju! Gaimon to Kimyou na Nakama

synopsis: On the legendary Treasure Island, Luffy and crew encounter strange animals and an even stranger man named Gaimon.

title.jp: Santouryuu no Kako! Zoro to Kuina no Chikai!

synopsis: In the past, young Zoro sparred constantly with a girl named Kuina, but he could never claim victory. They vowed that one of them would someday be the world's greatest swordsman - but tragedy intervened.

title.jp: Meibutsu Kokku! Kaijou Restaurant no Sanji

synopsis: The Straw Hats need a cook among their crew, so they head to a nearby restaurant and meet a passionate Sous Chef named Sanji.

title.jp: Manekarezaru Kyaku! Sanji no Meshi to Gin no On

synopsis: Luffy witnesses the fighting prowess and compassionate nature of the Sous Chef Sanji. The good news: The Going Merry's found a cook! The bad news: He has no intention of joining the crew!

title.jp: Saikyou no Kaizoku Kantai! Teitoku Don Krieg

synopsis: The staff and patrons of the Baratie panic when Don Krieg arrives! The starving pirate begs for nourishment, only to find himself denied. Unable to see a wretch starve, Sanji steps in once again.

title.jp: Mamore Baratie! Dai Kaizoku: Akaashi no Zeff

synopsis: Don Krieg promises further malice as he returns to his ship, but the threat to the Baratie proves short-lived as an even bigger threat arrives!

title.jp: Taka no Me no Mihawk! Kengou Zoro Umi ni Chiru

synopsis: The Going Merry's been stolen by Nami, and the showdown for possession of the Baratie is delayed. But the action's not dead in the water - Zoro challenges Hawk-Eye Mihawk to a duel!

title.jp: Hissatsu Ashiwaza Sakuretsu! Sanji vs Teppeki no Pearl

synopsis: The battle begins for possession of the Baratie, with Zeff leading the cooks against Krieg's pirates. Luffy and crew join the fray, but things aren't looking too good!

title.jp: Zeff to Sanji no Yume Maboroshi no All Blue

synopsis: Sanji recalls his childhood as an apprentice chef aboard a ship attacked by Red Foot Zeff! When the young Sanji found himself overboard, it was the fearsome captain himself who jumped to the rescue.

title.jp: Reitetsu Hijou no Kijin Kaizoku Kantai Souchou Gin

synopsis: As the battle for Baratie rages on, Luffy is forced to take a drastic course of action and Ghin debates where his loyalties lie.

title.jp: Shinanee yo! Gekitou Luffy vs Krieg!

synopsis: The scoundrel Don Krieg appears to have the upper hand in his fight with Luffy. To avoid walking the plank, the rubber man must try a different strategy.

title.jp: Shitou no Ketchaku! Hara ni Kukutta Ippon no Yari!

synopsis: The standoff between Luffy and Don Krieg takes a turn in favor of the Straw Hats when their captain focuses his onslaught on his opponent's weaponry.

title.jp: Tabidachi! Umi no Kokku wa Luffy to Tomo Ni

synopsis: With Don Krieg defeated, Luffy tries to convince Sanji to join up with the Straw Hats. The skilled cook is interested, but he has something to prove before moving on.

title.jp: Higashi no Umi Saiaku no Otoko! Gyojin Kaizoku Arlong!

synopsis: With their culinary concerns in good hands, the Straw Hats set off in search of Nami - who's on a collision course with a deadly foe!

title.jp: Kokoyashi Mura no Majo! Arlong no Onna Kanbu

synopsis: Zoro is captured by Fishman Arlong and learns a shocking secret about Nami. Unable to believe his ears, he puts the navigator to the ultimate test.

title.jp: Usopp Shisu? Luffy Jouriku wa Mada?

synopsis: Luffy and his crew make their way towards Arlong Park and a showdown with its fishy proprietor. Along the way, they discover a treasure map that raises more questions about Nami.

title.jp: Zenin Shuuketsu! Usopp ga Kataru Nami no Shinjitsu

synopsis: A fierce argument over where Nami's loyalties lie divides the Straw Hat Pirates and only one thing's for sure - no one is willing to risk their life for a traitor.

title.jp: Himerareta Kako! Onna Senshi Bellemere!

synopsis: Nami's adopted sister, Nojiko arrives to fill in some details about the skilled mapmaker's younger days.

title.jp: Ikinuke! Haha Bellemere to Nami no Kizuna!

synopsis: Nojiko continues the story of Nami's younger days. Back in the present, Nami gets agonizingly close to a long time goal, but betrayal looms on the horizon.

title.jp: Luffy Tatsu! Uragirareta Yakusoku no Ketsumatsu!

synopsis: Nezumi comes to confiscate Nami's treasure, but who's he working for? More importantly, who's Nami working for, and what's she gonna do with her booty?

title.jp: Luffy Dai Pinchi! Gyojin vs Luffy Kaizoku-dan

synopsis: The Straw Hats' faith in Nami is restored, and now it's time for a battle royal! Luffy and the gang are determined to make Arlong pay for mistreating their friend.

title.jp: Luffy Suibotsu! Zoro vs Tako no Hatchan

synopsis: The Straw Hats and Arlong's fishmen are locked in a swashbuckling slugfest, but things take a bad turn when Luffy gets trapped beneath the waves.

title.jp: Hokori Takaki Senshi! Gekitou Sanji to Usopp

synopsis: While his friends work to free the captain of the Straw Hats, cowardly Usopp finds himself in a position to shed his yellow streak and make his father proud.

title.jp: Luffy Zenkai! Nami no Ketsui to Mugiwara Boushi

synopsis: Nami must decide between letting Arlong maintain his hold over her, or joining the Straw Hats and leading the oppressed villagers against the tyrant fishman.

title.jp: Sakuretsu! Gyojin Arlong Umi Kara no Moukougeki!

synopsis: Arlong better watch his back-fins, because Captain Luffy knows about all the horrible things he did to Nami - and it makes his blood boil?

title.jp: Gyojin Teikoku no Owari! Nami wa Ore no Nakama da!

synopsis: Something about Nami's former prison gives Luffy an added burst of strength. He's so moved by her terrible past that he vows to destroy all of Arlong Park!

title.jp: Egao no Tabitachi! Saraba Kokyou Cocoyashi Mura

synopsis: After a grueling fight, Luffy defeats Arlong and succeeds in destroying his headquarters. The merry marauders enjoy the fruits of victory while Nami makes peace with her turbulent past.

title.jp: Shoukinkubi! Mugiwara no Luffy yo ni Shirewataru

synopsis: Finally, the day has arrived where Luffy's face is on an authentic wanted poster! Now there are enemies in hot pursuit as the crew makes waves for Logue Town - final resting place of Gold Roger!

title.jp: Mugiwara wo Oe! Chiisana Buggy no Dai Bouken

synopsis: Buggy gets marooned on an island inhabited by unusual creatures and tangles with the island's caretaker, Gaimon. If he is to finally destroy Luffy, Buggy must cast his lot with a mysterious woman.

title.jp: Omachi Ka Ne! Aa Fukkatsu no Buggy Senchou

synopsis: The Buggy Pirates fight each other for the right to take their lost captain's place. While they're busy beating each other's brains out, a cannibalistic tribe makes plans to have something special for dinner.

title.jp: Hajimari to Owari no Machi: Logue Town Jouriku

synopsis: The Straw Hats arrive at Logue Town, and each crewmember embarks upon a mission of a more personal nature. While his crew shops, Luffy goes in search of sacred ground.

title.jp: Sandai Kitetsu to Yubashiri! Zoro no Shintou to Josouchou

synopsis: Luffy has a run-in with Captain Smoker, and his failure to keep a low profile helps Buggy draw a bead on him. Elsewhere, Zoro takes a chance that his skill can overcome a dangerous curse.

title.jp: Usopp vs Kozure no Dadi Mahiru no Kettou

synopsis: Usopp finds an amazing pair of sharpshooter's goggles, but they lead to a run in with Daddy the Parent - the greatest gunslinger ever! Now, the Straw Hat marksman is headed for the deadliest of all duels.

title.jp: Hono no Ryouri Battle? Sanji vs Bijin Chef

synopsis: A cooking competition with the fiery chef Carmen rekindles Sanji's dreams of the legendary All Blue.

title.jp: Buggy no Revenge! Shokeidai de Warau Otoko!

synopsis: Buggy and his mysterious female ally trap Luffy on the same platform where Gold Roger was executed. He is to be killed for his offenses against Buggy, but Zoro and Sanji attempt a daring rescue mission.

title.jp: Densetsu wa Hajimatta! Mezase Idai Naru Kouro

synopsis: As a storm batters Logue Town, Buggy, Alvida, and Captain Smoker close in on Luffy for a stirring final showdown!

title.jp: Arata Naru Bouken no Yokan! Nazo no Shoujo Apis

synopsis: The discovery of a small girl adrift in an abandoned life boat interrupts Luffy and his crew’s voyage to the Grand Line.

title.jp: Kiseki no Ikimono! Apis no Himitsu to Densetsu no Shima

synopsis: After escaping the clutches of the Marine fleet, the Straw Hats soon find themselves in an equally dangerous predicament – stranded in the Calm Belt!

title.jp: Eric Shutsugeki! Gunkanjima Kara no Dai Dasshutsu!

synopsis: The Straw Hats want to return Apis’s dragon to his nest, but the Marines have them surrounded. Looks like it’s time for another daring escape!

title.jp: Zekkai no Kotou! Densetsu no Lost Island

synopsis: Even for Nami, finding the dragon’s lost island proves to be tougher than looking for a needle in a haystack – or at the bottom of the ocean.

title.jp: Haikyou no Kettou! Kinpaku no Zoro vs Eric!

synopsis: Nami discovers a map to the true location of the dragon’s nest, and Zorro puts his steel to the test against Eric the Whirlwind.

title.jp: Luffy Kanzen Houi! Teitoku Nelson no Hissaku

synopsis: The Straw Hats sail headfirst into Commodore Nelson and his Marine armada. While Luffy, Sanji, and Zoro dodge cannon balls, Eric the Whirlwind prepares a sneak attack!

title.jp: Ousora wo Mau Mono! Yomigaeru Sennen no Densetsu!

synopsis: With their rescue mission taking on water, the Straw Hats get some surprising help from the great blue yonder.

title.jp: Ikari no Ketchaku! Akai Dairiku wo Norikoero!

synopsis: Episode 61 is "half-filler" episode. The first half (00:00 - 13:00) is filler content which concludes the filler arc "Warship Island". The second half (13:00 - 24:00) is canon and the beginning of "Reverse Mountain" arc.

title.jp: Sasho no Toride? Kyodai Kujira Laboon Arawareru

synopsis: The Straw Hat crew takes a wild ride up and down a mountain only to end up in the belly of a giant whale that’s on the lookout for pirates!

title.jp: Otoko no Yakusoku! Luffy to Kujira Saikai no Chikai

synopsis: Luffy trades blows with Laboon the whale, and Nami is distressed to learn that navigating the Grand Line is no easy feat.

title.jp: Kaizoku Kangei no Machi? Whisky Jouriku

synopsis: A violent snow storm batters the crew of the Going Merry, but once the Straw Hats arrive at Whisky Peak, the locals invite them to a raucous celebration.

title.jp: Sakuretsu Santouryuu! Zoro vs Baroque Works

synopsis: There are bounty hunters on the prowl, and most of the Straw Hats are dead drunk. Only Zoro is still sober enough to hoist a sword.

title.jp: Shinken Shoubu! Luffy vs Zoro Nazo no Dai Kettou

synopsis: There’s a mysterious princess that needs protection from a nose-picking assassin, but Luffy and Zoro are too busy duking it out to worry about explosive boogers.

title.jp: Oujo Vivi wo Todokero! Luffy Kaizoku Dan Shukkou

synopsis: The Straw Hats depart Whisky Peak on a mission to return the Princess of Alabasta to her kingdom while protecting her from an army of vicious assassins.

title.jp: Ganbare Coby! Coby-Meppo Kaigun Funtouki

synopsis: While the crew heads for Little Garden with the princess, Luffy and Zoro’s old nemesis, Axe-Hand Morgan, escapes from a Marine prison ship.

title.jp: Coby-Meppo no Ketsui! Garp Chuushou no Oyagokoro

synopsis: Colby and Helmeppo train day and night to prove they’re tough enough to be Marines. A violent showdown with Vice-Admiral Garp will determine if they’re worth their salt.

title.jp: Taiko no Shima! Little Garden ni Hisomu Kage!

synopsis: Luffy’s gang is running low on supplies, so they stop at Little Garden to find something to eat. Unfortunately for them, it might end up the other way around.

title.jp: Dekkai Kettou! Kyojin Dorry to Brogy

synopsis: Not only are there dinosaurs running wild on the island of Little Garden, but the Straw Hats soon find themselves in the middle of a gargantuan grudge match.

title.jp: Luffy Okoru! Seinaru Kettou ni Hiretsu na Wana

synopsis: Usopp and Luffy are fascinated by the endless battle waged between Dorry and Broggy; however, fascination turns to outrage when Monkey catches a whiff of treachery.

title.jp: Broggy Shouri no Goukyuu! Elbaf no Ketchaku!

synopsis: Luffy’s blood boils for revenge against the assassins who sabotaged Dorry and Broggy’s battle, but he’s currently trapped between a rock and a hard place.

title.jp: Ma no Candle! Munen no Namida to Okari no Namida

synopsis: While Luffy struggles to free himself, his friends fall into the hands of Baroque Works. Though the odds are against them, the Straw Hats will never give up!

title.jp: Luffy wo Osou Maryoku! Colors Trap!

synopsis: Nami, Zoro, and the Princess are in danger of becoming exhibits in a fiendish artist’s collection, and only Luffy can save them. But he’s busy having a cup of tea.

title.jp: Iza Hangeki! Usopp no Kiten to Kaenboshi!

synopsis: With his friends about to be permanently entombed in wax, Usopp is provided with the perfect opportunity to be brave and make his father proud.

title.jp: Saraba Kyojin no Shima! Alabasta wo Mezase

synopsis: After narrowly avoiding death, Luffy’s crew and the Princess set sail for Alabasta, but something large and dangerous looms in their path.

title.jp: Nami ga Byouki? Umi ni Furu Yuki no Mukou ni!

synopsis: Nami comes down with a terrible fever and the Straw Hats don’t know what to do. Looks like the Grand Line might claim another victim.

title.jp: Kishuu! Bliking Gou to Blik no Wapol

synopsis: The Straw Hats continue their quest to find a doctor for Nami. Along the way, they deal with a ravenous invader and get a chilly reception from local islanders.

title.jp: Isha no Inai Shima? Na mo Naki Kuni no Bouken

synopsis: Luffy and Sanji make a bold trek up a snow-covered mountain in search of a witch who might hold the key to curing Nami.

title.jp: Happy Kai? Majo to Yobareta Isha!

synopsis: Ferocious, giant, snow rabbits slow Luffy and Sanji’s progress up the mountain. Meanwhile, the former king Wapol returns to the town he abandoned.

title.jp: Dalton no Kakugo! Wapol Gundan Shima ni Jouriku

synopsis: Nami hovers near death while Luffy and Sanji fend off the abominable rabbits. Back at the village, Dalton leads a revolt against the dastardly Wapol.

title.jp: Yuki no Sumi Shima! Drum Rockies wo Nobore!

synopsis: An unlikely source acts as a roadblock to give Luffy some climbing room, and Zorro emerges from a snow bank cold, cranky, and ready to rumble

title.jp: Tonakai wa Aoppana! Chopper no Himitsu!

synopsis: After a long journey up the mountain, Nami finally receives much-needed medical attention, but Sanji and Luffy are more interested in eating the doctor!

title.jp: Hamidashimono no Yume! Yabu Isha Hiluluk!

synopsis: Luffy recruits Tony Tony Chopper to join the Straw Hat crew as the ship’s doctor.

title.jp: Hiluluk no Sakura to Uketsugare Yuku Ishi!

synopsis: Chopper’s first friend was a quack doctor who couldn’t cure a cold, but the old man still managed to teach the little reindeer how to care for people.

title.jp: VS Wapol Gundan! Bakubaku no mi no Nouryoku!

synopsis: Luffy unleashes the full force of his Gum Gum fury on Wapol, and Chopper is amazed by the rubberman’s fierce devotion to the pirate flag.

title.jp: Zoan Kei Akuma no mi! Chopper Shichidan Hengei

synopsis: When Wapol orders his goons to attack the Straw Hats, Chopper shows off a little something he calls the Rumble Ball!

title.jp: Oukoku no Shihai Owaru Toki! Shinnen no Hata wa Eien ni

synopsis: Wapol attacks Nami in her weakened condition, but Monkey B. Luffy is quick to step in and even the odds.

title.jp: Hiluluk no Sakura! Drum Rockies no Kiseki

synopsis: After an explosive battle with Wapol, Luffy begins the tiring process of convincing Chopper to join his pirate gang.

title.jp: Sayounara Doramujima! Boku wa Umi e Deru!

synopsis: Chopper sets sail for Alabasta with his new friends, and Dalton thinks back to his first meeting with Princess Vivi.

title.jp: Alabasta no Eiyuu to Senjou no Ballerina

synopsis: The Straw Hats rescue a man of many faces as they approach Alabasta. Sure, he’s good for a laugh, but they may regret pulling him out of the drink.

title.jp: Iza Sabaku no Kuni e! Ame wo Yobu Kona to Hanrangun

synopsis: The Straw Hats arrive in Alabasta with precious little time to stop the rebellion. Sanji and Chopper are sent to gather supplies for a dangerous trip across the desert.

title.jp: Gouketsutachi no Saikai! Yatsu no na wa Hiken no Ace

synopsis: Captain Smoker has Luffy in his grasp until a fiery stranger creates a diversion, giving the Straw Hats a chance to make a break for it.

title.jp: Ace to Luffy! Atsuki Omoi to Kyoudai no Kizuna

synopsis: Ace and Luffy’s happy reunion is crudely interrupted by the Billions of Baroque Works. They may be outnumbered, but these brothers are no ordinary pirates!

title.jp: Midori no Machi Erumalu to Kung fu Jugon!

synopsis: Before they can start their trek across the desert, Luffy and the Straw Hats are stopped at the shore by the cute – but formidable – Kung Fu Dugongs.

title.jp: Suna no Kuni no Bouken! Ennetsu no Daichi ni Sugomu Mamono

synopsis: Luffy’s crew encounters treacherous birds and man-eating foliage on its desert odyssey, and just when they think the coast is clear, a great disturbance emerges from beneath the sand!

title.jp: Sabaku no Kaizokudan Toujou! Jiyuu ni Ikiru Otokotachi

synopsis: The Straw Hats cross paths with the Barbar Sand Pirates, and Ace runs into big trouble when he gets separated from the group.

title.jp: Nisemono no Iji! Kokoro no Hanrangun Kamyu!

synopsis: Princess Vivi devises a plan to test the hearts of a gang of so-called rebels. They talk a good game, but will their bite measure up to their bark?

title.jp: Hanrangun Senshi Kohza! Vivi ni Chikatta Yume!

synopsis: The Straw Hats continue their journey to Yuba, where a bittersweet reunion with a childhood friend awaits Princess Vivi.

synopsis:
The much-anticipated wedding cake is on its way, but there is a debate at the last minute! Shouldn't this opportunity be used to slip poison into Big Mom's meal to topple the Emperor of the Sea? Meanwhile, Carrot's unearthly ability based on the power of the moon saves the day!

(Source: Crunchyroll)

title.en: Finally, They Clash! The Emperor of the Sea vs. the Straw Hats!

synopsis:
Luffy, through sheer force of will, can almost use his Haki to battle Katakuri! Meanwhile, the Sunny catches fire while the Straw Hats try to kick out Big Mom but that’s when Jimbei steps up to the plate and takes a swing at her!

(Source: Crunchyroll)

title.en: Dark King's Direct Precepts! The Battle Against Katakuri Turns Around!

synopsis:
Luffy tries to enhance his Haki to foresee Katakuri’s next move but Katakuri’s attacks keep pulling him down! However, when he summons every bit of wisdom from his training with Rayleigh, he remembers something important that could turn the tables for him! 

(Source: Crunchyroll)

title.en: Finally He Returns! Sanji, the Man Who'll Stop the Emperor of the Sea!

synopsis:
The cake is finally prepared and brought before Big Mom! With the end of her vicious rampage in sight, there is a chance for the Straw Hats to flee! Big Mom's crew is forced to decide who to attack! Meanwhile, Luffy grows ever closer to using his Haki! 

(Source: Crunchyroll)
